{"id":"300779618_Degrees_of_Unsolvability_A_Tutorial","abstract":"Given a problem \\(P\\), one associates to \\(P\\) a degree of unsolvability, i.e., a quantity which measures the amount of algorithmic unsolvability which is inherent in \\(P\\). We focus on two degree structures: the semilattice of Turing degrees, \\(\\mathcal {D}_\\mathrm {T}\\), and its completion, \\(\\mathcal {D}_\\mathrm {w}=\\widehat{\\mathcal {D}_\\mathrm {T}}\\), the lattice of Muchnik degrees. We emphasize specific, natural degrees and their relationship to reverse mathematics. We show how Muchnik degrees can be used to classify tiling problems and symbolic dynamical systems of finite type. We describe how the category of sheaves over \\(\\mathcal {D}_\\mathrm {w}\\) forms a model of intuitionistic mathematics, known as the Muchnik topos. This model is a rigorous implementation of Kolmogorov’s nonrigorous 1932 interpretation of intuitionism as a “calculus of problems”.","authors":["Stephen G. Simpson"],"meta":["June 2015","DOI:10.1007/978-3-319-20028-6_9","Conference: Conference on Computability in Europe"],"references":["266591162_New_directions_in_computability_and_randomness","231746808_Interpretability_and_Definability_in_the_Recursively_Enumerable_Degrees","226234172_Embeddings_into_the_Medvedev_and_Muchnik_lattices_of_P01_classes","319394544_Undecidable_Theories","307555318_Mass_problems_and_density","304405348_On_computable_numbers_with_an_application_to_the_Entscheidungsproblem","300569296_THE_TURING_DEGREES_AN_INTRODUCTION","291188094_On_the_degrees_of_complete_extensions_of_arithmetic","274403757_Forcing_with_Bushy_Trees","270151834_Degrees_of_Unsolvability","270150099_IMM_Introduction_to_metamathematics","268976847_Word_problems_II_The_Oxford_book","268644762_The_Hierarchy_Based_on_the_Jump_Operator","268605071_Recursive_function_theory_Proceedings_of_the_5th_Symposium_in_Pure_Mathematics_of_the_American_Mathematical_Society_held_in_New_York_April_6-7_1961_Corr_repr_of_the_1962_o